; GT4Amiga program watcher
; Polls GT4A:incoming/trigger for a new program to run.
; Runs the program, captures output to serial port.
; Place this in GT4A:s/gt4amiga-watcher on the shared drive.
;
; Output from the program is captured via SER: (serial device).
; Programs write to their stdout (Output() handle); the >SER: redirect
; sends it to the TCP socket that GToolkit listens on.
; The completion marker (see done-marker file) signals end to the host.
;
; NOTE 1: AmigaDOS 1.3 has no "SKIP BACK" (added in 2.0), so a label+Skip
; loop cannot go backward. Instead this script re-invokes itself at the
; end. It uses Run (not Execute) to relaunch as a fresh detached process
; and then exits immediately - using Execute here would nest each iteration
; inside the previous one (parent waits for child), growing the process
; stack without bound until it eventually crashes silently after a few
; minutes of polling.
;
; NOTE 2: "Echo ... >SER:" fails with "Invalid argument to ECHO" on this
; AmigaDOS 1.3 setup, even though Copy/Dir redirection to SER: works fine.
; So the completion marker is a static file, sent via Copy instead of Echo.
;
; NOTE 3: comments containing double angle-bracket sequences confuse this
; Execute's parser once a real redirection appears later in the script
; (fails with "EXECUTE: No K directive"). Avoid those characters in comments.

IF EXISTS GT4A:incoming/trigger
  ; Remove trigger first to avoid re-run
  Delete GT4A:incoming/trigger QUIET

  ; Run the binary directly (NOT Execute, which runs scripts)
  GT4A:incoming/program >SER:

  ; Send completion marker so GT knows output is finished
  Copy GT4A:s/gt4amiga-done-marker SER:
ENDIF
Wait 1
Run >NIL: Execute GT4A:s/gt4amiga-watcher
